Phase 7 - Guardrails & Hardening:
	- Implement confidence threshold logic: zero results OR below BM25 score floor → soft refusal; log redacted query + failure type + document_type to unanswered query log @done(2026-04-22) @added(2026-04-12)
	- Add scope guardrails: attempt retrieval first; if nothing found, return warm redirect explaining what CivicPulse can help with @done(2026-04-22) @added(2026-04-12)
	- Block response delivery if no source citation present (same unified soft-refusal message as low-confidence refusal) @done(2026-04-22) @added(2026-04-12)
	- Configure LLM provider budget cap and usage alert (provider-agnostic; ops-only alert, no user-facing degradation) @added(2026-04-12)
	- Add system prompt instruction to refuse queries seeking private information about named individuals (two-layer defense: clean vault sources + prompt backstop) @done(2026-04-22) @added(2026-04-22)
	- Build criteria-elicitation dialogue for evaluative/political questions (e.g. "Is [official] doing a good job?" → elicit user's criteria → retrieve facts against those criteria; agent never takes a position) @done(2026-04-22) @added(2026-04-22)
	- Build context-aware soft-refusal messages distinguishing: future/recent events not yet scraped, hyperlocal specifics (contact Town Hall), wrong jurisdiction (county/state/federal) @done(2026-04-22) @added(2026-04-22)
	- Test adversarial prompts (political bias, off-topic, PII extraction attempts) @done(2026-04-22) @added(2026-04-12)
	- Test "I don't know" behavior across edge cases (future events, hyperlocal, wrong jurisdiction, low-score retrieval) @done(2026-04-22) @added(2026-04-12)

